1
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:49,840
Is it such a coincidence?

2
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:51,640
Grandma.

3
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:53,560
Grandma.

4
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:57,520
What is it?

5
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:59,080
What is it?

6
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:01,740
Is this a photo of Xigui Tea Mountain?

7
00:01:03,080 --> 00:01:03,840
This mountain?

8
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:06,080
Yes. It is Xigui Tea Mountain.

9
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:08,410
Why does it look different now?

10
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:09,520
Come with me.

11
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:11,120
Come with me.

12
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:17,880
This is Xigui Mountain.

13
00:01:18,160 --> 00:01:21,840
In 1999,

14
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:25,080
a swarm of pests attacked the tea leaves.

15
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:27,680
The mountain suffered a severe infestation.

16
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,400
I get it.

17
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,460
What do you get?

18
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:31,880
Translate it.

19
00:01:33,880 --> 00:01:36,080
Grandma wants you to let me start a band.

20
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,330
I'll look for it myself.

21
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:41,840
Let me take you there.

22
00:01:50,479 --> 00:01:51,120
Brother.

23
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,970
What are you recording?

24
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:53,840
Nothing.

25
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:55,410
Brother.

26
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,640
Think about my proposal just now.

27
00:01:58,080 --> 00:01:59,560
I'll help you find the person.

28
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,600
Room and board included.

29
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:01,680
You help me form a band.

30
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:02,540
It's a win-win.

31
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:04,120
I'll use him to find the person first.

32
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:05,050
Then I'll leave.

33
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,400
Let's get one thing straight.

34
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,440
I'll only be the band manager. I won't go on stage.

35
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,100
It's a deal.

36
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:10,240
Watch the road.

37
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,770
But if you don't go on stage,

38
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,860
who will play lead?

39
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:17,840
That's the place.

40
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:19,620
The tea mountain in the photo.

41
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:22,079
This is where I got off on my first day.

42
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:24,360
In the middle of nowhere.

43
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,200
Are you sure?

44
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:25,890
Let's go.

45
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,600
I'll show you what the Lincang know-it-all can do.

46
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:28,520
Slow down.

47
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,040
Charge!

48
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:33,700
Easy on the gas.

49
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:34,480
Isn't our Lincang beautiful?

50
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:35,920
Faster.

51
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:38,800
Go!

52
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,880
Slow down.

53
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:52,840
The path on this mountain

54
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,840
was changed after the infestation.

55
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:57,100
I'm the only one who knows the way.

56
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,120
Pretty impressive, right?

57
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:59,120
Very impressive.

58
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,800
It's twistier than the pilgrimage to the West.

59
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,600
My mom says I act like a monkey.

60
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:06,120
A Lincang Monkey King and a Master from Beijing.

61
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,380
This combo is perfect.

62
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:10,250
Why don't we name our band Journey to the West?

63
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:11,450
Journey to the West?

64
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:14,560
But I don't want to go through the 81 tribulations.

65
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:15,400
Bro,

66
00:03:16,079 --> 00:03:17,280
don't you want to know

67
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:19,120
how I know this path?

68
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:22,240
This is a famous haunted house.

69
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:24,560
My friends and I explored here once.

70
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,130
A haunted house?

71
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:26,960
Bro,

72
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,920
are you afraid of ghosts?

73
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:31,079
No, I'm not.

74
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,040
Let's go.

75
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:36,760
Be careful.

76
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:38,360
Slow down.

77
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:49,930
Who's there?

78
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,960
Who? You're seeing things.

79
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:53,360
A ghost!

80
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:56,079
It's a society under the rule of law. There are no ghosts.

81
00:03:56,079 --> 00:03:57,340
I was just teasing you.

82
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,000
Brother.

83
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,920
Maybe we should forget about it.

84
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,380
Let's come back tomorrow.

85
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:08,800
We're already here.

86
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,200
I'm not afraid of people.

87
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:12,010
Why would I be afraid of ghosts?

88
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:21,339
But that's exactly what's scary.

89
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:25,960
Let's go.

90
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,460
Bro, what's wrong?

91
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:46,080
I think I stepped on

92
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,920
something moving.

93
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:57,159
This place

94
00:04:57,440 --> 00:05:00,170
must be a temporary resting spot for tea farmers.

95
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:01,880
It's this drum.

96
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:03,640
What?

97
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:06,170
There's nothing special about it.

98
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,400
Yanwang held a drum just like this in the photo.

99
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,060
The style is exactly the same.

100
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:12,080
This totem is indeed rare,

101
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,730
but wooden drums in Lincang

102
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:17,970
are probably more common than people named Yanwang.

103
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,659
I still want to ask.

104
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:38,720
If you don't go on stage, who will play the lead?

105
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,640
You. I think you can do it.

106
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:43,200
Do you have an electric guitar?

107
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:43,760
No.

108
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,800
I only have the acoustic guitar my dad bought me.

109
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,659
Okay. Let's pick out a suitable instrument for you.

110
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:50,640
Thanks, bro.

111
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:54,960
Bro, do you eat Jianshouqing mushrooms?

112
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:55,640
Bro.

113
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,840
What kind of drum do you want?

114
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:27,800
Hello.

115
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,760
Have you seen this drum?

116
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:37,080
This drum...

117
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:38,800
Brother, have you seen it?

118
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,560
Of course.

119
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,480
When I took it to film a movie,

120
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,980
the director followed me around all day,

121
00:06:45,120 --> 00:06:46,250
calling me Brother.

122
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:47,610
Impressive.

123
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:50,000
So, Brother, is the drum still with you?

124
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,680
It's just that...

125
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:55,640
it requires a small token of appreciation.

126
00:06:58,520 --> 00:06:59,450
Are you in a band?

127
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:02,000
Yeah, just formed.

128
00:07:02,880 --> 00:07:04,610
I've been making stars lately.

129
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,760
I can be your agent.

130
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:07,760
Do you know the Tang Dynasty band?

131
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,690
I single-handedly launched them.

132
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:10,820
Here is my card.

133
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,040
Here.

134
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,970
Just call me Brother Jiang.

135
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:16,490
Call him Brother Jiang.

136
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,600
I am his agent.

137
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,520
An agent, huh?

138
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:23,880
What bands have you managed?

139
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:24,760
Let's hear it.

140
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:26,520
I play pop music.

141
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:27,720
I don't play rock.

142
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,040
Bubblegum pop.

143
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,440
Sucking up to platforms.

144
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,520
Got it.

145
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:35,480
Don't give me that sarcastic attitude.

146
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,840
When my brother was headlining music festivals,

147
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:38,480
you were still playing with rubber bands.

148
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,360
Kid,

149
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,520
you're full of hot air.

150
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:42,920
With a face like that,

151
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:43,920
music festivals?

152
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:46,480
He should take a good look in the mirror.

153
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:50,880
Let him go.

154
00:07:52,159 --> 00:07:52,880
Bro!

155
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,730
How dare you hit my brother!

156
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,000
Let go!
